udel.GardenProject.plants

Class Plant

  • java.lang.Object
    • udel.GardenProject.plants.Plant
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Plant
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    For every plant, there is a corresponding Plant object that contains as much information that can be loaded by PlantLoader.

    Plant data was gathered from public domain sources using Python scripts, and the plant data is stored as .json files in main.udel.plants.data
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Team 0

      • Plant

        public Plant(java.lang.String[] commonNames,
             java.lang.String latinName,
             java.lang.String description,
             boolean[] bloomTime,
             double light,
             Moisture moisture,
             SoilTypes soilType,
             Canopy canopy,
             boolean delawareNative,
             boolean invasive,
             PlantDataSource[] source,
             java.lang.String[] images)
        Constructor.
        Parameters:
        commonNames - Alternative friendly names for plants.
        latinName - Official Linnaeus name, Genus species.
        description - Non-standard description with all extra information gathered from JSON files.
        bloomTime - 12-element boolean array, one for each month. True if it blooms during that month, false if not.
        light - From 0.0 to 1.0, percentage of light the plant requires.
        moisture - See Moisture enum.
        soilType - See SoilType enum.
        canopy - See Canopy enum.
        delawareNative - True if the plant is native to Delaware, U.S.A., false if not.
        invasive - True if invasive, false if not.
        source - See PlantDataSource enum.
        images - String array of HTTP links to images of plant.

        public java.util.HashSet<Colors> getColors()
